Preconditions:
The grid must be a 2-dimensional array.
The grid must have at least one row and one column.
Each element in the grid must be a non-negative integer.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the minimum cost required to make the grid have at least one valid path.
The grid should remain unchanged after the method is executed.
The minimum cost should be calculated based on the given grid and the rules for creating a valid path.
The method should return -1 if it is not possible to create a valid path in the grid.